4. Changes in local.inc on the GForge server
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Please add the followings to GForge's local.inc configuration file:

$sys_default_git_server='git.localgarage';
$sys_default_git_root='projects';
$sys_default_git_use_dav='true';
$sys_default_git_use_ssl='true';
$sys_default_git_remote_user='www-data';
$sys_default_git_ssh_key='/home/www-data/.ssh/id_rsa';
$sys_default_git_type_command='/usr/local/bin/git_repo_type.sh';

$sys_default_git_server specifies the server where the Git repositories will 
be hosted. It can also be set to 'localhost', if the local machine runs Git.

$sys_default_git_root is related again the web server configuration. If you 
specified a subdirectory for the repositories, then add it here.

Cloning the git repository based on the example configuration above will happen
like this:

 git clone https://git.localgarage/projects/someproject

$sys_default_git_remote_user, $sys_default_git_ssh_key are necessary to 
complete the repository access changes from within the SCM admin page. 

Setting the "Enable Anonymous Access" will trigger an action on the remote 
Git server.
In the example configuration the action is run by 'www-data' who connects to 
'git.localgarage' using the '/home/www-data/.ssh/id_rsa' ssh key. On the server
'www-data' will run the '/usr/local/bin/git_repo_type.sh' script to reset the 
Apache settings for the repository in question.

 
5. Enable the plugin in GForge
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The 'Site Admin' tab on the GForge web interface has a 'Plugin Manager'
page where you can activate plugins on a site wide basis. 
 
Be sure to do that if you want this plugin to be available to projects.


